the ice-truck killer.

32
00:03:10,276 --> 00:03:11,060
Bullshit.

33
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:12,990
<i>Of course I agree
with my sister,

34
00:03:13,085 --> 00:03:15,331
<i>but unlike her, I'm not upset.

35
00:03:15,438 --> 00:03:18,493
<i>He's still out there,
and I'm waiting...

36
00:03:19,145 --> 00:03:20,442
<i>breathless.

37
00:03:37,095 --> 00:03:40,391
<i>I find people around me are always
making some kind of connection,

38
00:03:40,477 --> 00:03:43,301
<i>like friendship or romance,

39
00:03:43,536 --> 00:03:46,681
<i>but human bonds always lead
to messy complications...

40
00:03:46,775 --> 00:03:48,651
<i>commitment, sharing,

41
00:03:48,888 --> 00:03:51,703
<i>driving people to the airport.

42
00:03:51,825 --> 00:03:53,891
<i>Besides, if I let
someone get that close,

43
00:03:53,998 --> 00:03:56,652
<i>they'd see who
I really am...

44
00:03:56,687 --> 00:03:59,032
<i>and I can't let that happen.

45
00:04:00,285 --> 00:04:02,822
So, time to put on my mask.

46
00:04:06,336 --> 00:04:09,190
- I need your expertise.
- I live to serve.

47
00:04:09,448 --> 00:04:10,943
Excuse us, fellas.

48
00:04:15,877 --> 00:04:20,163
- Interesting hand job.
- That's funny.

49
00:04:20,767 --> 00:04:22,502
It is?

50
00:04:24,578 --> 00:04:27,262
So, how long you think
it's been there?

51
