be almost delicate.

63
00:05:11,055 --> 00:05:13,750
You see between the first
and second row of carpals...

64
00:05:14,177 --> 00:05:15,912
Very surgical.

65
00:05:17,768 --> 00:05:20,582
Check out what else
he left behind.

66
00:05:22,066 --> 00:05:25,542
A little postcard
to remember him by.

67
00:05:30,816 --> 00:05:34,721
- How far is Rand Beach from here?
- This is Rand Beach.

68
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:38,250
It was renamed Petrie
Beach a few years ago.

69
00:05:50,546 --> 00:05:52,251
Okay, everybody.

70
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:58,961
Everybody say "stinky feet".

71
00:05:59,097 --> 00:06:00,083
Stinky feet!

72
00:06:01,215 --> 00:06:03,943
Wait. Nobody move.
Dexter, were you smiling?

73
00:06:04,086 --> 00:06:05,960
- No.
- Okay, we'll do another one.

74
00:06:06,057 --> 00:06:08,351
This time, everybody smiles.
You, too, Dex.

75
00:06:08,446 --> 00:06:10,181
Yeah, pretend you're
burning ants.

76
00:06:10,275 --> 00:06:12,781
- Shut your damn face, Deb.
- Hey, language, please.

77
00:06:12,815 --> 00:06:14,402
What?
She always talks like that.

78
00:06:14,437 --> 00:06:16,923
Enough, you two.
Dexter, come here.

79
00:06:22,126 --> 00:06:23,790
What's your problem?

80
00:06:23,815 --> 00:06:25,192
I hate the beach.

81
00:06:25,206 --> 00:06:27,351
It's sandy and gross and
nasty, and I want to go home.

82
00:06:27,487 --> 00:06:30,121
Too bad.
You're part of a family.

83
00:06:30,226 --> 00:06:33,042
And being part of a family
means smiling for photos.

84
00:06:33,315 --> 00:06:36,141
Why should I
pretend I'm happy?

85
00:06:36,278 --> 00:06:39,620
Because it'll make
your mom happy,

86
00:06:41,425 --> 00:06:43,631
and because it's
how you fit in.

87
00:06:43,768 --> 00:06:46,353
- Remember we talked about that?
- Yeah.

88
00:06:46,547 --> 00:06:48,042
This is how you do it.

89
00:06:48,175 --> 00:06:49,972
When somebody takes your picture,
you smile.

90
00:06:50,006 --> 00:06:52,211
It doesn't matter if
you're happy or not.

91
00:06:52,406 --> 00:06:54,890
You just do it to fit in.
Okay?

92
00:06:54,986 --> 00:06:57,102
- Okay.
- All right.

93
00:06:59,646 --> 00:07:01,223
Come here, handsome.

94
00:07:02,568 --> 00:07:09,111
Okay. Everybody ready?
One more time.

95
00:07:11,406 --> 00:07:13,283
Stinky feet!

96
00:07:16,758 --> 00:07:19,953
Yeah, I just need to stop by my
apartment to pick up a few labs.

97
00:07:20,095 --> 00:07:23,103
Straight to the station after, yeah.
Thanks, lieutenant.

98
00:07:34,848 --> 00:07:36,862
<i>Dexter Morgan,

99
00:07:37,098 --> 00:07:38,832
<i>this is your life.

100
00:07:40,817 --> 00:07:44,773
<i>It is my new friend --
The ice-truck killer.

101
00:07:45,058 --> 00:07:48,602
<i>When he broke into my apartment,
he took some time to get to know me...

102
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:49,612
<i>my life...

103
00:07:51,688 --> 00:07:53,423
<i>my secrets.

104
00:08:04,575 --> 00:08:07,251
...have even brought in
manpower from other counties

105
00:08:07,386 --> 00:08:09,183
in an effort to
expedite the search.

106
00:08:09,317 --> 00:08:12,310
Officially, Mr. Tucci has not
been charged with any crime...

107
00:08:12,317 --> 00:08:15,052
Then tell the fucking governor
to free up funds for overtime.

108
00:08:15,097 --> 00:08:18,571
I mean the more guys I got out there,
the sooner we find Tucci.

109
00:08:19,728 --> 00:08:21,983
Kelly, I'll get back to you.

110
00:08:25,086 --> 00:08:27,133
What's wrong?

111
00:08:27,148 --> 00:08:30,202
Fingerprint I. D. came back
on that hand from the beach.

112
00:08:30,215 --> 00:08:31,452
It belongs to Tony Tucci,

113
00:08:31,478 --> 00:08:33,921
your ice-truck killer suspect.

114
00:08:34,057 --> 00:08:35,153
What?

115
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:42,521
Wait a minute.

116
00:08:42,627 --> 00:08:44,973
No. No, no, no. No way.

117
00:08:45,158 --> 00:08:47,881
No way!
I mean, this --

118
00:08:48,208 --> 00:08:49,752
This has to be a mistake!

119
00:08:49,777 --> 00:08:52,103
The mistake, Maria, was
unleashing a high-profile manhunt

120
00:08:52,128 --> 00:08:54,700
before you had all the facts.

121
00:08:56,506 --> 00:08:58,121
Fuck!

122
00:09:01,638 --> 00:09:06,042
Okay. This doesn't mean that
Tucci is not the killer.

123
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:07,512
Don't!

124
00:09:07,737 --> 00:09:10,513
Just... just don't.

125
00:09:11,537 --> 00:09:13,662
You wanted to be on tv --
well, get ready...

126
00:09:13,697 --> 00:09:16,320
'cause the press will
annihilate us for this.

127
00:09:16,418 --> 00:09:19,242
We'll be lucky if Tucci's
mother doesn't file a lawsuit.

128
00:09:22,155 --> 00:09:23,512
All right.

129
00:09:24,527 --> 00:09:28,010
You go talk to that woman.
Do your mea culpas.

130
00:09:28,157 --> 00:09:29,653
If we handle this right,

131
00:09:30,436 --> 00:09:32,593
maybe we can mitigate
the fallout.

132
00:09:32,787 --> 00:09:33,662
Tom!

133
00:09:34,896 --> 00:09:36,900
I'm the last person
she wants to see.

134
00:09:36,917 --> 00:09:38,901
I called her son a killer!

135
00:09:39,088 --> 00:09:41,323
And now's your chance
to make it right.

136
00:10:00,837 --> 00:10:03,452
So Laguerta screwed the
pooch on this one, huh?

137
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:04,843
I'm taking point.

138
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:07,693
You can help by getting all
non essentials off the beach.

139
00:10:07,725 --> 00:10:09,843
Secure and separate any witnesses,
all right?

140
00:10:09,877 --> 00:10:13,883
Will do. What did the Captain say?
Did he make her cry?

141
00:10:18,418 --> 00:10:20,991
Just control the
fucking beach, Angel.

142
00:10:24,097 --> 00:10:26,003
I knew Tucci wasn't the killer.
I knew it.

143
00:10:26,026 --> 00:10:27,620
Laguerta whipped
up a manhunt

144
00:10:27,633 --> 00:10:28,895
for a rent-a-cop.

145
00:10:28,930 --> 00:10:31,411
Man, I wish I could have been there
to see the Captain rip her a new one.

146
00:10:31,411 --> 00:10:33,397
Morgan, calm down.

147
00:10:33,539 --> 00:10:35,981
Laguerta insulted the real
killer's intelligence,

148
00:10:36,115 --> 00:10:39,041
and now he's getting back at us
for chasing after the wrong guy.

149
00:10:39,078 --> 00:10:40,803
You see all these
people over here?

150
00:10:40,837 --> 00:10:42,573
- Yeah.
- What are they?

151
00:10:42,945 --> 00:10:44,532
Potential witnesses.

152
00:10:44,707 --> 00:10:47,301
And what do we do with
potential witnesses, Morgan?

153
00:10:47,338 --> 00:10:51,332
We -- we interview them.
Got it.

154
00:11:00,935 --> 00:11:02,601
Where is he...

155
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,871
The rest of him?

156
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:11,273
We're -- we're still looking.

157
00:11:11,595 --> 00:11:14,373
The entire force is looking.
We're making every effort.

158
00:11:14,695 --> 00:11:16,763
Are you sure it's
Tony? Because...

159
00:11:17,318 --> 00:11:18,200
Yes.

160
00:11:20,057 --> 00:11:21,742
I'm afraid so.

161
00:11:26,945 --> 00:11:28,201
Mrs. Tucci...

162
00:11:30,248 --> 00:11:33,183
I said some very harsh
things about your son.

163
00:11:33,278 --> 00:11:34,260
Thank you.

164
00:11:38,568 --> 00:11:41,521
"Thank you"?
For what?

165
00:11:41,937 --> 00:11:46,691
- For coming to tell me in person.
- For God's sake, please.

166
00:11:47,098 --> 00:11:49,303
There's nothing more
important than this.

167
00:11:49,537 --> 00:11:52,821
Can you find my son's body?

168
00:11:52,925 --> 00:11:55,013
If it's the last thing I do.

169
00:11:55,166 --> 00:11:56,682
I made a grave...

170
00:11:56,696 --> 00:12:00,682
Bring him home, please.

171
00:12:00,828 --> 00:12:03,720
I just want to bury my son.

172
00:12:18,177 --> 00:12:20,003
I do love Halloween.

173
00:12:20,196 --> 00:12:23,250
- What's inside of a pumpkin?
- See for yourself.

174
00:12:24,225 --> 00:12:28,531
You don't like this stuff?
I do. Come on. Get in there.

175
00:12:31,087 --> 00:12:34,183
I'll finish cleaning this out.
You can carve it tomorrow.

176
00:12:35,847 --> 00:12:38,103
There he is again, mom.

177
00:12:38,338 --> 00:12:40,631
My god.
It's every night now.

178
00:12:40,825 --> 00:12:42,571
That dog?
Where's it coming from?

179
00:12:42,646 --> 00:12:44,762
Next door --
My neighbor's.

180
00:12:44,907 --> 00:12:47,452
Leaves the poor thing in
the yard all day and night.

181
00:12:47,488 --> 00:12:50,131
It's been getting worse.
I mean, I would talk to her,

182
00:12:50,258 --> 00:12:52,182
but I don't want to
start something.

183
00:12:52,508 --> 00:12:55,130
Listen to him, mom.
He's so sad.

184
00:12:55,256 --> 00:12:58,272
I just wish he would shut
up so I could sleep.

185
00:12:58,408 --> 00:12:59,951
Do you want me to talk to her?

186
00:13:00,276 --> 00:13:02,202
No, you don't have to do that.

187
00:13:06,047 --> 00:13:07,582
I insist.

188
00:13:30,335 --> 00:13:33,821
Hello.
I don't think we've met.

189
00:13:34,005 --> 00:13:36,670
Boyfriend of the blonde next door.
I've seen you around.

190
00:13:36,705 --> 00:13:38,500
Look, I'm just getting in.
I'm tired.

191
00:13:38,515 --> 00:13:40,013
That's precisely why I'm here.

192
00:13:40,068 --> 00:13:44,852
We can't help but notice your dog,
uh, cries... a lot.

193
00:13:44,947 --> 00:13:47,632
I know.
My ex moved out and left his dog.

194
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:51,470
Trust me,
I wish there was something I could do.

195
00:13:51,657 --> 00:13:54,221
You could, uh, take him inside.

196
00:13:54,415 --> 00:13:56,473
Walter's an outside dog.

197
00:13:56,615 --> 00:13:58,913
You put Walter inside,
Walter's an inside dog.

198
00:13:58,916 --> 00:14:00,882
He doesn't like being inside.

199
00:14:01,626 --> 00:14:03,412
Did he tell you that?

200
00:14:06,497 --> 00:14:10,213
We'd really appreciate it if you
could find a way to keep him quiet.

201
00:14:10,255 --> 00:14:11,642
The kids are upset.

202
00:14:11,677 --> 00:14:13,652
Maybe that's 'cause they think their
crackhead father is gonna come back

203
00:14:13,845 --> 00:14:15,793
and beat their asses again.

204
00:14:18,245 --> 00:14:20,643
You know what works
for me? Earplugs.

205
00:14:30,807 --> 00:14:34,331
<i>I could make things so
much easier for Rita...

206
00:14:35,815 --> 00:14:37,550
<i>but that would be wrong.

207
00:14:44,765 --> 00:14:46,953
<i>I love Halloween --

208
00:14:47,276 --> 00:14:49,632
<i>the one time of year when
everyone wears a mask...

209
00:14:49,675 --> 00:14:51,613
<i>not just me.

210
00:14:52,538 --> 00:14:55,853
<i>People think it's fun to
pretend you're a monster.

211
00:14:55,886 --> 00:14:58,943
<i>Me, I spend my life
pretending I'm not.

212
00:15:00,008 --> 00:15:05,400
<i>Brother, friend, boyfriend...
All part of my costume collection.

213
00:15:09,228 --> 00:15:11,623
<i>Some people might
call me a fraud.

214
00:15:11,705 --> 00:15:14,183
OK.
Let's see if it will fit.

215
00:15:17,035 --> 00:15:20,103
You stabbed me in the back!

216
00:15:20,207 --> 00:15:23,603
<i>I prefer to think of myself
as a master of disguise.

217
00:15:25,835 --> 00:15:27,673
They're so excited.

218
00:15:27,775 --> 00:15:30,630
Sure they are. They get to binge
on sugar for an entire day.

219
00:15:30,656 --> 00:15:31,983
Who wouldn't love that?

220
00:15:32,006 --> 00:15:35,682
What about a costume for you?
Maybe this one?

221
00:15:36,975 --> 00:15:41,542
No. No. I think I'll be Snow White
again. It's kind of tradition.

222
00:15:42,787 --> 00:15:45,033
Dexter, look.
I'm a princess, too.

223
00:15:45,265 --> 00:15:47,940
Just like your mom --
Two perfect princesses.

224
00:15:49,388 --> 00:15:51,281
Let me guess.
You're gonna be a dwarf.

225
00:15:51,448 --> 00:15:54,450
No way.
I want to be Joe from "Blue's Clues. "

226
00:15:54,545 --> 00:15:57,981
I keep telling him that a
rugby shirt is not a costume.

227
00:16:06,126 --> 00:16:08,851
<i>Another photo from
my family album.

228
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:13,170
<i>He's re-creating my past with
Tony Tucci's body parts.

229
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:15,801
<i>He's forcing me to see this.

230
00:16:15,947 --> 00:16:18,950
Nobody paying you to stand
around and goddamn stare.

231
00:16:19,368 --> 00:16:22,330
I thought Angel was working
this case, Sergeant.

232
00:16:23,766 --> 00:16:25,211
Sergeant?

233
00:16:28,455 --> 00:16:29,811
Friends of yours?

234
00:16:30,347 --> 00:16:33,120
Don't worry about it.
Worry about this.

235
00:16:33,407 --> 00:16:36,792
The foot was severed between
the tarsus and the metatarsus.

236
00:16:36,926 --> 00:16:39,593
The wound is circular --
again, almost surgical.

237
00:16:40,938 --> 00:16:44,412
And there's blood. Guy gives us
body after body with no blood.

238
00:16:44,646 --> 00:16:47,941
- Why he's making a switch now?
- He's trying to send a message...

239
00:16:48,037 --> 00:16:51,510
One that's more important than his
ritual need to drain the blood and

240
00:16:51,658 --> 00:16:52,921
wrap the parts.

241
00:16:53,338 --> 00:16:57,243
- Okay, so what's the message?
- I'm not sure.

242
00:16:57,386 --> 00:17:02,713
- Well, who's he sending it to?
- I can't tell you that, either.

243
00:17:03,777 --> 00:17:06,263
What fucking good are you?

244
00:17:07,187 --> 00:17:10,533
No fucking good at all,
