00:34:13,248 --> 00:34:14,361
Smile!

488
00:34:18,537 --> 00:34:19,912
What do we have?

489
00:34:20,147 --> 00:34:22,680
Ankle to knee.
He's moving up the leg.

490
00:34:26,245 --> 00:34:28,503
You think Tucci's still alive?

491
00:34:29,615 --> 00:34:32,321
If he is, he won't be for long.

492
00:34:37,315 --> 00:34:39,812
Unless you're toting
a portable DVD player,

493
00:34:40,046 --> 00:34:42,071
you better be finished watching
that security footage.

494
00:34:42,105 --> 00:34:44,641
I am on break.
I'm on my own time.

495
00:34:44,968 --> 00:34:48,292
So you are,
but your shift starts in two hours.

496
00:34:48,438 --> 00:34:50,780
So if I were you,
I'd head back to the station.

497
00:34:50,926 --> 00:34:52,941
Traffic at this hour's a bitch.

498
00:34:54,556 --> 00:34:56,532
Speaking of bitch...

499
00:34:57,965 --> 00:35:00,931
Didn't dad bring us here
once when we were kids?

500
00:35:01,118 --> 00:35:02,231
I don't remember.

501
00:35:02,566 --> 00:35:04,760
Hey, Dexter, come here.
Take a look at this.

502
00:35:04,817 --> 00:35:05,792
Excuse us.

503
00:35:06,726 --> 00:35:09,262
She's right, you know,
about the traffic.

504
00:35:13,517 --> 00:35:15,610
It's interesting. There's
no sign of infection

505
00:35:15,628 --> 00:35:17,513
where the foot was cut off,
like he gave Tucci

506
00:35:17,546 --> 00:35:20,542
prophylactic antibiotics
before amputating.

507
00:35:21,245 --> 00:35:23,642
At least he's looking
after his patient.

508
00:35:25,117 --> 00:35:27,612
Hey, check this out.

509
00:35:28,905 --> 00:35:31,393
Is this appropriate?

510
00:35:32,276 --> 00:35:33,961
It's our anniversary...

511
00:35:34,385 --> 00:35:36,020
and it's the big one.

512
00:35:36,995 --> 00:35:39,293
Nina deserves the best.

513
00:35:41,005 --> 00:35:43,090
"Ox"?

514
00:35:43,307 --> 00:35:46,121
No. Fuck!

515
00:35:46,498 --> 00:35:49,013
What's the matter with you?
It's x's and o'S.

516
00:35:49,046 --> 00:35:50,601
Like tic-tac-toe?

517
00:35:50,627 --> 00:35:53,675
No, like "hugs and kisses".

518
00:35:53,675 --> 00:35:58,293
Diamond-filled hugs and kisses
in a white-gold setting.

519
00:35:58,317 --> 00:36:00,941
Well, that's good,
'cause you wouldn't want it to look like

520
00:36:00,965 --> 00:36:03,422
someone's playing
tic-tac-toe on her head.

521
00:36:08,127 --> 00:36:09,861
Goddamn it.

522
00:36:16,015 --> 00:36:17,561
Where's mom?

523
00:36:17,707 --> 00:36:20,773
She had to run a few errands before
she takes you two trick-or-treating.

524
00:36:20,806 --> 00:36:22,903
But I'm too tired to
go trick-or-treating.

525
00:36:23,377 --> 00:36:25,491
I heard you two were
up a lot last night.

526
00:36:25,636 --> 00:36:27,653
It was that damn dog.

527
00:36:27,837 --> 00:36:30,321
Hey, Code,
grown-up language is for grown-ups.

528
00:36:30,558 --> 00:36:33,201
I don't think that dog will
be bothering you anymore.

529
00:36:33,236 --> 00:36:36,241
- How do you know?
- My mystic powers told me.

530
00:36:36,387 --> 00:36:39,012
Heard Lindsay Lohan say "damn".

531
00:36:39,156 --> 00:36:41,191
All right, tell you what --
I'll make you a deal.

532
00:36:41,226 --> 00:36:44,280
When you become a rock star,
you can swear, too.

533
00:36:44,375 --> 00:36:50,313
- Walter! Walter!
- You're right. He's gone.

534
00:36:51,748 --> 00:36:54,332
Where's my dog?!
What did you do with it?!

535
00:37:12,715 --> 00:37:14,592
All right. Here he is.

536
00:37:14,905 --> 00:37:20,032
Just remember to walk him,
feed him, and love him, okay?

537
00:37:21,657 --> 00:37:25,180
My nieces are shy sometimes.
Girls, say thank you to Rita.

538
00:37:25,286 --> 00:37:26,731
Thank you.

539
00:37:27,657 --> 00:37:30,710
They already made a doggy bed --
sweaters, towels.

540
00:37:30,906 --> 00:37:33,252
It actually looks more
comfortable than my bed.

541
00:37:33,716 --> 00:37:35,812
I knew this would
be a perfect fit.

542
00:37:36,698 --> 00:37:39,322
You did a good thing, Rita.
Thank you.

543
00:37:44,786 --> 00:37:47,362
<i>Harry was the only
one who saw me...

544
00:37:47,465 --> 00:37:49,620
<i>...really saw me...

545
00:37:49,715 --> 00:37:51,591
<i>So he taught me to hide.

546
00:37:51,615 --> 00:37:54,243
<i>That's what's kept me safe.

547
00:37:54,487 --> 00:37:58,580
<i>But sometimes, I'm not sure where
Harry's vision of me ends

548
00:37:58,607 --> 00:38:01,063
<i>and the real me starts.

549
00:38:01,925 --> 00:38:04,460
<i>If I'm just a collection
of learned behaviors...

550
00:38:04,646 --> 00:38:07,752
<i>bits and pieces of Harry...
maybe my new friend is right.

551
00:38:07,935 --> 00:38:10,143
<i>Maybe I am a fraud.

552
00:38:25,206 --> 00:38:27,933
- Hi.
- Hey.

553
00:38:32,517 --> 00:38:34,671
Where's Astor and Cody?

554
00:38:34,815 --> 00:38:38,391
They're passed out in a
sugar coma at Colleen's.

555
00:38:40,335 --> 00:38:47,720
- Can I come in?
- Yeah, sure. Sorry.

556
00:38:53,598 --> 00:38:57,071
I should warn you,
I haven't really been myself lately.

557
00:38:57,358 --> 00:39:00,362
Maybe I can cheer you up.

558
00:39:06,246 --> 00:39:08,442
Trick or treat.

559
00:39:14,136 --> 00:39:15,971
You look great.

560
00:39:21,885 --> 00:39:24,903
- Who are you?
- Lara Croft.

561
00:39:25,736 --> 00:39:29,313
"Tomb Raider".

562
00:39:29,498 --> 00:39:33,453
You raid tombs dressed like that?
That's impressive.

563
00:39:35,255 --> 00:39:37,043
What happened to Snow White?

564
00:39:37,318 --> 00:39:39,711
Well, I'm -- I'm sick of her.

565
00:39:42,816 --> 00:39:44,591
You know, I never did

566
00:39:44,828 --> 00:39:48,210
get to thank you for
picking the kids up for me.

567
00:39:48,758 --> 00:39:50,962
You took care
of your "errand"?

568
00:39:51,198 --> 00:39:52,083
Yes.

569
00:39:52,316 --> 00:39:55,563
The beagle has landed happily in
the arms of two loving girls.

570
00:39:55,887 --> 00:39:57,810
You are a superhero.

571
00:40:04,236 --> 00:40:08,191
It was such an incredible
feeling rescuing that dog.

572
00:40:08,886 --> 00:40:11,713
You upset your neighbor.

573
00:40:12,956 --> 00:40:14,270
Fuck her.

574
00:40:17,365 --> 00:40:21,681
Well, I guess you're used to dealing
with people like her, right?

575
00:40:22,148 --> 00:40:24,492
Considerably worse.

576
00:40:24,728 --> 00:40:28,300
Is that why you haven't
been yourself lately?

577
00:40:28,768 --> 00:40:32,341
There's a case I just can't
seem to get out of my mind.

578
00:40:35,166 --> 00:40:37,702
Maybe I can help.

579
00:40:38,676 --> 00:40:42,211
No. I'm afraid there's
nothing you can do.

580
00:40:42,488 --> 00:40:45,072
Oh, I don't know.

581
00:40:45,307 --> 00:40:48,793
I'm a dognapper now...
and a tomb raider.

582
00:40:49,066 --> 00:40:52,741
There's all sorts
of things I can do.

583
00:41:04,678 --> 00:41:06,971
What -- what are you doing?

584
00:41:07,626 --> 00:41:09,642
Whatever I want.

585
00:41:13,348 --> 00:41:16,641
<i>I've come to appreciate the
comfortable moments with Rita...

586
00:41:16,826 --> 00:41:19,481
<i>The easy, quiet moments--

587
00:41:21,528 --> 00:41:22,692
<i>This...

588
00:41:24,317 --> 00:41:26,001
<i>...might be better.

589
00:41:29,567 --> 00:41:31,963
Look, there's Mr.
Tub-of-Lardy bringing

590
00:41:32,196 --> 00:41:34,962
Mrs. Tub-of-Lardy another
bucket of fried chicken.

591
00:41:41,476 --> 00:41:44,792
- Where's your brother?
- I'm not his keeper.

592
00:41:47,046 --> 00:41:49,010
What do you think of this?

593
00:41:51,328 --> 00:41:54,053
It's an anniversary
present for Nina.

594
00:41:54,477 --> 00:41:57,773
See, it's...
it's a diamond key to my heart.

595
00:41:58,787 --> 00:42:00,903
It's... it's a key,

596
00:42:01,045 --> 00:42:03,293
but, you see,
it's shaped like a heart.

597
00:42:03,438 --> 00:42:05,892
You can't tell me that it
looks like anything else,

598
00:42:05,927 --> 00:42:08,842
'cause that's what it is.
That's it. That's what I like.

599
00:42:09,027 --> 00:42:11,041
And I'm not gonna take it back.

600
00:42:11,418 --> 00:42:14,750
It's perfect, Angel.
She'll love it.

601
00:42:15,065 --> 00:42:16,323
Really?

602
00:42:17,575 --> 00:42:18,841
I would.

603
00:42:24,167 --> 00:42:26,932
How... How do I look?
Like the tie?

604
00:42:36,698 --> 00:42:38,143
Angel.

605
00:42:39,358 --> 00:42:41,742
Happy anniversary, baby.

606
00:42:42,115 --> 00:42:45,412
You know you can't just
walk in here anymore.

607
00:42:51,058 --> 00:42:52,742
I just thought...

608
00:42:54,648 --> 00:42:56,873
...our anniversary...

609
00:42:59,288 --> 00:43:02,481
Maybe tonight we could
put all that behind us.

610
00:43:03,456 --> 00:43:05,471
It doesn't matter
what night it is.

611
00:43:06,165 --> 00:43:08,283
I told you I need time.

612
00:43:08,428 --> 00:43:11,243
It's been three months, baby.

613
00:43:11,936 --> 00:43:13,723
How much time do you need?

614
00:43:14,028 --> 00:43:16,611
Don't turn this around
on me, Angel...

615
00:43:16,798 --> 00:43:18,800
...Not after what you did.

616
00:43:20,146 --> 00:43:23,242
I need as much time as I need.

617
00:43:31,527 --> 00:43:32,983
Angel...

618
00:43:37,607 --> 00:43:42,031
As long as you're here,
you want to see Aury?

619
00:43:55,868 --> 00:43:58,073
Lo siento, princesa.

620
00:43:59,837 --> 00:44:02,601
Lo siento, lo siento,
lo siento.

621
00:44:32,926 --> 00:44:33,860
Thank you.

622
00:44:50,048 --> 00:44:51,541
That was...

623
00:44:56,036 --> 00:44:57,571
...unexpected.

624
00:44:58,877 --> 00:45:01,462
Yeah.
For me, too.

625
00:45:05,067 --> 00:45:07,182
I have no problem with...

626
00:45:08,018 --> 00:45:09,272
unexpected.

627
00:45:11,316 --> 00:45:12,573
No, you...

628
00:45:12,838 --> 00:45:14,382
certainly don't.

629
00:45:23,078 --> 00:45:25,561
I have to get back to the kids.

630
00:45:28,997 --> 00:45:31,012
What are these?

631
00:45:33,738 --> 00:45:38,070
I've been reorganizing
my photos a little.

632
00:45:38,377 --> 00:45:42,521
Look how cute you are.

633
00:45:42,845 --> 00:45:47,361
And your dad --
such a nice face, just like you.

634
00:45:48,246 --> 00:45:52,533
- I was adopted.
- I know.

635
00:45:52,716 --> 00:45:56,292
But you're both good men.
I can tell.

636
00:46:01,538 --> 00:46:03,033
Very poetic.

637
00:46:03,357 --> 00:46:05,752
Poetic?
It's a water fountain.

638
00:46:06,638 --> 00:46:10,631
Well, yeah, but look at the
way your dad took the photo.

639
00:46:10,777 --> 00:46:13,313
His shadow's on the
wall right next to you.

640
00:46:13,408 --> 00:46:15,242
It's like he's always with you.

641
00:46:15,978 --> 00:46:17,623
I'd frame this one.

642
00:46:19,475 --> 00:46:22,151
<i>All this time the
answer was right here.

643
00:46:22,425 --> 00:46:25,893
<i>Harry... photographer and
foster father extraordinaire.

644
00:46:26,128 --> 00:46:30,033
<i>He is always with me,
and he's the common denominator.

645
00:46:30,218 --> 00:46:31,393
Rita...

646
00:46:32,775 --> 00:46:34,932
you're a genius.

647
00:46:37,257 --> 00:46:39,741
<i>All those years of
smiling for the camera...

648
00:46:39,976 --> 00:46:44,973
<i>It was empty and fake,
the pictures meaningless, until now.

649
00:46:45,568 --> 00:46:47,400
<i>Pictures of Harry.

650
00:47:03,178 --> 00:47:07,173
So this is it.

651
00:47:07,318 --> 00:47:08,380
It's cool.

652
00:47:09,725 --> 00:47:10,711
Cool.

653
00:47:11,956 --> 00:47:15,253
Dexter, this is the
place where my father,

654
00:47:15,398 --> 00:47:18,782
your grandfather,
worked for 30 years.

655
00:47:18,928 --> 00:47:20,842
He started out as the janitor,

656
00:47:20,985 --> 00:47:23,292
worked his way up to
chief of maintenance.

657
00:47:23,428 --> 00:47:26,150
This place put
food on our table.

658
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:28,362
In two weeks,
it'll all be shut down.

659
00:47:28,495 --> 00:47:29,100
I know.

660
00:47:29,797 --> 00:47:32,281
Excuse me, miss! Miss?

661
00:47:32,568 --> 00:47:35,193
- Would you mind?
- Oh, come on, dad.

662
00:47:39,457 --> 00:47:41,371
Hey, you all right?

663
00:47:41,566 --> 00:47:45,140
It's nothing.
Bad medianoches for lunch. I'm okay.

664
00:47:45,286 --> 00:47:47,773
I'm sorry, miss.
It's okay. Thanks.

665
00:47:47,955 --> 00:47:49,891
We're not gonna be needing a picture,
after all.

666
00:47:49,927 --> 00:47:50,760
Yeah, we are.

667
00:47:50,977 --> 00:47:52,911
Dex, I really don't feel
like doing this now.

668
00:47:52,947 --> 00:47:54,020
Don't be a baby --

669
00:47:54,256 --> 00:47:57,401
Being part of a family means
smiling for family photos, right?

670
00:48:07,988 --> 00:48:09,801
<i>My friend left this.

671
00:48:10,037 --> 00:48:11,720
<i>He's showing me where to go.

672
00:48:13,575 --> 00:48:16,060
<i>Am I going because
it's what he wants

673
00:48:16,207 --> 00:48:18,411
<i>or because that's what
Harry would want?

674
00:48:20,676 --> 00:48:22,791
<i>What do I want?

675
00:48:51,116 --> 00:48:54,680
<i>The hospital's shut down now,
abandoned for years,

676
00:48:54,876 --> 00:48:57,882
<i>but tonight it's
visiting hours again.

677
00:49:29,415 --> 00:49:30,911
Well, James...

678
00:49:32,905 --> 00:49:36,521
Why did you have to be such
a pain in the ass, huh?

679
00:49:41,567 --> 00:49:43,630
Fuck !

680
00:49:43,868 --> 00:49:46,313
I didn't tell you
you could get up.

681
00:50:03,666 --> 00:50:06,291
Please, please.

682
00:50:10,085 --> 00:50:11,912
Now you get up.

683
00:50:19,226 --> 00:50:22,191
You traumatize my little
girl in church...

684
00:50:22,975 --> 00:50:26,981
break the knees of
my best turner.

685
00:50:29,566 --> 00:50:32,673
You're a wild dog, Sergeant.

686
00:50:34,345 --> 00:50:36,970
The only thing to do
with a wild dog...

687
00:50:37,716 --> 00:50:39,873
Police!
Hands in the air!

688
00:50:46,128 --> 00:50:48,421
Thought you could use backup.

689
00:50:48,608 --> 00:50:51,193
You could have filled me in,
man. Shit.

690
00:50:52,357 --> 00:50:55,640
Got you going after a
goddamn cop, motherfucker.

691
00:50:56,208 --> 00:50:58,463
We own your ass now.

692
00:51:01,095 --> 00:51:02,743
So this was the
plan all along...

693
00:51:02,877 --> 00:51:05,552
To use me as bait to
bring down Guerrero?

694
00:51:06,528 --> 00:51:09,872
Yeah, and now my sister
can rest in peace.

695
00:51:10,475 --> 00:51:13,382
We're done now, Doakes.
We're even.

696
00:51:13,665 --> 00:51:16,103
I'll call this in,
bring the paramedics.

697
00:51:16,386 --> 00:51:18,533
Get this piece of
shit out of here.

698
00:51:55,877 --> 00:51:57,090
Please.

699
00:52:01,486 --> 00:52:02,841
Just do it.

700
00:52:05,846 --> 00:52:06,543
Kill me.

701
00:52:09,327 --> 00:52:10,302
I'm ready.

702
00:52:22,165 --> 00:52:24,323
Just don't cut me anymore.

703
00:52:27,795 --> 00:52:30,283
Please don't cut me anymore.

704
00:52:31,165 --> 00:52:33,753
<i>Gift-wrapped and
begging for death.

705
00:52:33,898 --> 00:52:35,290
<i>Tools at the ready.

706
00:52:35,528 --> 00:52:36,932
Just kill me.
It's okay.

707
00:52:37,168 --> 00:52:39,400
<i>He was left here so
I would kill him,

708
00:52:39,546 --> 00:52:42,883
<i>but my new friend doesn't see
me as clearly as he thinks.

709
00:52:43,858 --> 00:52:46,022
<i>I can't kill this man.

710
00:52:46,208 --> 00:52:47,793
<i>Harry wouldn't want it.

711
00:52:48,868 --> 00:52:50,690
<i>And neither would I.

712
00:53:11,668 --> 00:53:12,593
Are you Morgan?

713
00:53:12,735 --> 00:53:14,660
Message came through
dispatch for you.

714
00:53:20,878 --> 00:53:22,610
Who left this?

715
00:53:24,216 --> 00:53:25,571
Who left it?!

716
00:53:36,356 --> 00:53:38,893
Jesus, stop that.
I'm getting bruises.

717
00:53:39,076 --> 00:53:40,482
I'm sorry.
I'm so excited.

718
00:53:40,715 --> 00:53:42,160
Try a hug once in a while.

719
00:53:45,125 --> 00:53:47,423
I don't know who your
contacts are, Morgan,

720
00:53:47,528 --> 00:53:49,061
but you are my up-and-comer.

721
00:53:49,257 --> 00:53:50,943
You saved a man's life tonight.

722
00:53:51,497 --> 00:53:53,612
I'm just the one who
got the call, Sir.

723
00:53:53,845 --> 00:53:55,713
But you followed it up.

724
00:53:55,817 --> 00:53:57,681
Right place at the
right time, Sir.

725
00:53:57,828 --> 00:54:00,173
- Where we at?
- Morgan's tip was good.

726
00:54:00,318 --> 00:54:02,291
They're taking Tucci
over to county.

727
00:54:02,386 --> 00:54:05,482
- Alive?
- Alive.

728
00:54:11,547 --> 00:54:15,531
So, I suppose this gets Deb
off of surveillance-tape duty.

729
00:54:15,947 --> 00:54:19,002
Really?
Is that what you suppose?

730
00:54:19,188 --> 00:54:20,733
I got your page, Lieutenant.

731
00:54:20,968 --> 00:54:22,710
Doakes is caught up
in the Guerrero bust.

732
00:54:22,745 --> 00:54:24,860
- You're taking point here.
- You got it.

733
00:54:25,005 --> 00:54:27,773
I'm tired of chasing this guy's shadow.
I want forensic evidence.

734
00:54:27,807 --> 00:54:31,212
I don't care if you have to tear
apart this building brick by brick.

735
00:54:31,247 --> 00:54:32,691
- Entiende?
- Si.

736
00:54:32,885 --> 00:54:34,710
Use Morgan here.

737
00:54:40,508 --> 00:54:42,751
How did your wife like that necklace,
Angel?

738
00:54:42,947 --> 00:54:44,412
